1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: Leatherby's Ice cream, cold house vodka, slightly-skewed food truck.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: Meet a family who converted an old auto shop into a hip barber garage, two sisters who sell sweet treats, and a woman who taps into the foodie culture. Discover how a hi-tech entrepreneur learned from his past mistakes to find success.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Take to the skies and explore how one vintage airplane buff turned his passion into a successful business. Meet an Elk Grove baker whose artistic frosting sculptures look too amazing to eat. Discover how a Sacramento man is using reclaimed wood to make beautiful furniture.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Patrick and Bobbin Mulvaney share their secret to running one of the country's top-rated restaurants, Mulvaney's B&L. In Roseville, visit Amitis Pourarian's THE STUDIO Martial Arts & Fitness to see how her can-do philosophy on life impacts her business. Also, will a Stockton couple be successful in their effort to bring life back to their business?

5.title: The Nightshift
5.plot: When the sun goes down, these entrepreneurs get to work. Meet the people pursuing their business dreams after hours. From a rapping taxi owner to delivering warm cookies and cold milk, creativity and ingenuity pay off.

10.title: Episode 110
10.plot: A Bay Area couple leaves behind their urban life to start a unique "farm to tap" brewery in the foothills near Lincoln. Twin brothers serving in Sacramento's fire and law enforcement departments find success using their family's BBQ recipes. Go inside a restored Woodland wool mill turning animal fibers into yarn. A full-service musical instrument store finds a niche in ukuleles.

11.title: Episode 111
11.plot: Discover the story behind a Thai restaurant that's become an institution in midtown Sacramento. Meet a Sacramento entrepreneur whose passion is to get America healthy and moving. See why an artisan furniture maker moved his business from the Bay Area to Stockton. And explore what it takes to operate a successful dance studio.

imdb.plot outline: Yes. We're Open introduces you to people who saw an opportunity to realize their ambitions and take their lives in an entirely different direction. Meet the entrepreneurs who said goodbye to their 9 to 5 jobs, realized their dreams, and tapped into their creative spirit.
